<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">6. Budget and commercial</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">
  The programme is supported by match funding from the NHS partner, paid to the Observatory, which
  contracts for delivery. The indicative budget envelope for the build and private beta is
  <strong>[to be confirmed]</strong>. Proposals should present clear value for money and a costed,
  phased plan. The procurement will run via <strong>[to be confirmed — e.g. an appropriate public
  procurement framework]</strong>.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">7. Who we are looking for</h2>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Demonstrable experience delivering accessible, user-centred public or health services to the NHS or GOV.UK service standards.</li>
  <li>A track record of secure, assured delivery (IG, clinical safety, identity) and of working in the open.</li>
  <li>Genuine capability and commitment to co-production with seldom-heard communities.</li>
  <li>A multidisciplinary team (user research, design, engineering, delivery, clinical safety).</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">8. How to respond</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">Proposals should be concise and address:</p>
<ol class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--number">
  <li>Your understanding of the problem and the people it affects.</li>
  <li>Your proposed approach, phasing and ways of working (including co-production and accessibility).</li>
  <li>How you will meet the assurance and technical requirements in section 3.</li>
  <li>Relevant experience and case studies, and the team you would assign.</li>
  <li>A costed, phased plan and how you ensure value for money.</li>
  <li>Risks and how you would manage them.</li>
</ol>

